enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve modifying the state of the bag by adding or removing elements from a collection.
Both methods involve removing elements from the bag, though removeAll removes multiple elements at once.
After calling removeAll, the bag should no longer contain any of the elements that were removed, which can be verified using containsAll.
Both methods modify the bag to retain or remove specific elements, making retainAll a good candidate for asserting the opposite behavior of removeAll.
